column1: gedit is the official text editor of the GNOME desktop environment. While aiming at simplicity and ease of use, gedit is a powerful general purpose text editor.
column3: gedit azali mobɔngele nkomá mokonzi ya nzíngazínga ya biló GNOME.  Soki olongi ésaleli ya pasi tɛ̂ mpe ya makasi tɛ̂, gedit azali mobɔngele nkomá ya makasi ya bosaléli banso.

column1: Whether you are writing the next bestseller, programming an innovative application, or simply taking some quick notes, gedit will be a reliable tool to accomplish your task.
column3: Te okoma best-seller ékoya, pologami ya sika, to mpe olingi kazwa ndambo ya noti, gedit azali esaleli ya kitoko mpona kokokisa misala na yo.

column1: Its flexible plugin system allows you to tailor the application to your needs and adapt it to your workflow.
column3: sistɛ́mɛ na ye ya kotíngisa epesi yo ndingisa ya kosalela esáliseli na mposa na yo mpe na lolenge na yo ya mosala.

column1: Whether to use the system's default fixed width font for editing text instead of a font specific to gedit. If this option is turned off, then the font named in the \"Editor Font\" option will be used instead of the system font.
column3: Lakisa soki ebongi kosalela bonene ya polosi likwa ya sistɛ́mɛ mpona libongeli nkoma na esika ya kosalela polosi moko ya gedit. Soki liponi wana eza ya kokangama, na tango wana polosi oyo éponami na liponi \" Polosi ya ebɔngeli\" eko salelama na esika ya polosi ya sistɛ́mɛ.

column1: A custom font that will be used for the editing area. This will only take effect if the \"Use Default Font\" option is turned off.
column3: Polosi ya koúlinisa nde esalelami na étando ya libongeli . Ekoki ko zwa esika soki liponi ya \"Salela polosi likwa\" ekangami.

column1: The ID of a GtkSourceView Style Scheme used to color the text.
column3: ID ya libɔngisi nzenga ya GtkSourceView bisaleli mpona botiyi langi ya nkoma

column1: Whether gedit should create backup copies for the files it saves.
column3: Lakisa soki gedit akoki kokela kopí ya bobíkisi ba kasa oyo azali ko bombisa

column1: Whether gedit should automatically save modified files after a time interval. You can set the time interval with the \"Autosave Interval\" option.
column3: Lakisa soki gedit akoki ko bombisa ya mɛ́i kasa eye ebóngolámí sima ya ntaka ya ngonga. Okoki kotiya ntaka ya ngonga na lopini \"ntaka ya mɛ́i-bombómbisi\".

column1: Number of minutes after which gedit will automatically save modified files. This will only take effect if the \"Autosave\" option is turned on.
column3: Motango ya miniti oyo sima na yango nde gedit akoki ko bombisa ye mɛ́i kasa ebóngolámí. Ekoki ko zwa esika soki liponi ya \"mɛ́i-bombómbisi\" ézali polélé.
Suka ya mutaya ya ekelá bwakisami

column1: Maximum number of actions that gedit will be able to undo or redo. Use \"-1\" for unlimited number of actions.
column3: Mutaya ya suka ya bikelá oyo gedit akoki kobákwisa to kozóngela. Salela \"-1\"  soki olingi kotiya ndelo tɛ̂.

column1: Specifies how to wrap long lines in the editing area. Use \"none\" for no wrapping, \"word\" for wrapping at word boundaries, and \"char\" for wrapping at individual character boundaries. Note that the values are case-sensitive, so make sure they appear exactly as mentioned here.
column3: Lakisa ndenge ya kokabola ba linie ya milayi na kati ya étando ya libɔngeli. Salela \"none\"  soki olingi kokabola tê, \"word\" pona kokabola na suka ya lokoma, mpe \"char\" pona kokabola na ndélo ya mokoma.  Yeba té mbenza bana bizali na botáli likomá, Sale té émonana ndengé étiyami.

column1: Last split mode choice for line wrapping mode
column3: Bopɔni ya suka na mode ya bokaboli linie

column1: Specifies the last split mode used with line wrapping mode, so that when wrapping mode is off we still remember the split mode choice. Use \"word\" for wrapping at word boundaries, and \"char\" for wrapping at individual character boundaries.
column3: Tiya bopɔni ya suka na mode ya bokaboli linie, mpo mode oyo étikala na  memuále ata soki fɔksío wana ékangami. Salela \"word\" pona kokabola na suka ya lokoma, mpe \"char\" pona kokabola na ndélo ya mokoma.

column1: Specifies the number of spaces that should be displayed instead of Tab characters.
column3: Tiya motuya ya sipasi oyo ékomonisama na ésika ya  monkoma ya lipipi.

column1: Whether gedit should insert spaces instead of tabs.
column3: Lakisa tango gedit alingi kokóákisa sipasi to tabulation

column1: Whether gedit should enable automatic indentation.
column3: Lakisa tango gedit alingi kolamusa bobéndi otomatíki

column1: Whether gedit should display line numbers in the editing area.
column3: Lakisa tango gedit alingi kolakisa mamɛlo ya liníɛ na kati ya étando ya libɔngeli.

column1: Whether gedit should highlight the current line.
column3: Lakisa tango gedit alingi kongengisa liníɛ ya sikawa.
Ngengisa bilembo ya botangoli oyo ekokani

column1: Whether gedit should highlight matching brackets.
column3: Lakisa soki gedit akoki kongengisa bilembo ya botangoli oyo ekokani

column1: Whether gedit should display the right margin in the editing area.
column3: Lakisa soki gedit akoki komonisa marzi nelómi nakati ya etando ya libɔngeli

column1: Specifies the position of the right margin.
Whether gedit should display the overview map for the document.
column3: Lakisa soki gedit akoki komonisa calati ya bomoni lisanga ya ba dokima
Ndéngé ya motifi ya simasima ya dokima

column1: Whether the document will get a background pattern painted.
column3: Lakisa soki dokima akozwa motifi ya simasima ya kokóba.

column1: Specifies how the cursor moves when the HOME and END keys are pressed. Use \"disabled\" to always move at the start/end of the line, \"after\" to move to the start/end of the line the first time the keys are pressed and to the start/end of the text ignoring whitespaces the second time the keys are pressed, \"before\" to move to the start/end of the text before moving to the start/end of the line and \"always\" to always move to the start/end of the text instead of the start/end of the line.
column3: Lakisa ndenge nini motúmbé azali kotambola tango tusi ya yambo mpe ya suka éfinami. Salela \"disabled\"  (ékangami)  pona kokende tango inso liboso/suka ya linie,  \"after\" (sima) pona kokende liboso/suka ya linie na ngonga  ya yambo oyo ba tusi bifinami mpe liboso/suka ya nkoma nakobosanaka ba sipasi, na tango ya ibalé oyo ba tusi bifanami, \"before\" (liboso) pona kokende liboso/suka ya linie liboso ya kokende liboso/suka ya linie mpe \"always\" (tango inso) pona kokende tango inso liboso/suka ya nkoma na ésika ya liboso/suka ya linie.

column1: Whether gedit should restore the previous cursor position when a file is loaded.
column3: Lakisa soki gedit akoki kozongisa motúmbé na ésika éleki tango ya kotombisa kasa.

column1: Whether gedit should enable syntax highlighting.
column3: Lakisa soki gedit akoki kolamusa bongengisi sɛtákisi

column1: Whether gedit should highlight all the occurrences of the searched text.
column3: Lakisa soki gedit akoki kongengisa ba okilansɛ niɔ́nsɔ ya boluki nkoma
Laka liníɛ ya suka ya sika

column1: Whether gedit will ensure that documents always end with a trailing newline.
column3: Lakisa soki gedit akoki ko keba te ba dokima esila ntángo ínsɔ na linie ya sika na suka ya kasa.

column1: Whether the toolbar should be visible in editing windows.
column3: Lakisa soki ndáko ya bisáleli akoki komónisama na lininisa ya libɔngeli

column1: Specifies when to show the notebook tabs. Use \"never\" to never show the tabs, \"always\" to always show the tabs, and \"auto\" to show the tabs only when there is more than one tab. Note that the values are case-sensitive, so make sure they appear exactly as mentioned here.
column3: Tiya ndengé ya komonisa  lipipi ya lininisa. Salela  \"never\"  mpona komonisa yango tê,  \"always\" mpona komonisa yango seko, mpe \"auto\" mpona komonisa yango soki éleki moko.  Yeba té mbenza bana bizali na botáli likomá, Sale té émonana ndengé étiyami.

column1: Whether the status bar at the bottom of editing windows should be visible.
column3: Lakisa soki  barɛ ya stati na nsé ya lininisa ya libɔngeli ekoki komonana.

column1: Whether the side panel at the left of editing windows should be visible.
column3: Lakisa soki pano ya mopanzi na embembé ya lininisa ya libɔngeli ekoki komonana.
Nsúka ya ba kásá ya sikawa

column1: Specifies the maximum number of recently opened files that will be displayed in the \"Recent Files\" submenu.
column3: Lakisa motuya ya suka ya ba kasa biwuti kofungolama biyé bikomonisama na méni-mwǎna \"Kasa ya sikawa\".

column1: Whether gedit should print syntax highlighting when printing documents.
column3: Lakisa soki gedit akoki kobimisa bongengisa sɛtákisi tango ya bobimisi ya ba dokima.

column1: Whether gedit should include a document header when printing documents.
column3: Lakisa soki gedit akoki kotiya likoló lia lonkásá tango ya bobimisi ya ba dokima.
Bimisa na mode ya bozongi na linie

column1: Specifies how to wrap long lines for printing. Use \"none\" for no wrapping, \"word\" for wrapping at word boundaries, and \"char\" for wrapping at individual character boundaries. Note that the values are case-sensitive, so make sure they appear exactly as mentioned here.
column3: Lakisa ndenge ya kokabola ba linie ya milayi tango ya bobimisi. Salela \"none\"  soki olingi kokabola tê, \"word\" pona kokabola na suka ya lokoma, mpe \"char\" pona kokabola na ndélo ya mokoma.  Yeba té mbenza bana bizali na botáli likomá, Sale té émonana ndengé étiyami.

column1: If this value is 0, then no line numbers will be inserted when printing a document. Otherwise, gedit will print line numbers every such number of lines.
column3: Soki mbenza oyo ézali 0, numelo moko tê ya linie éko koakisama tango ya bobimisi dokima. Soki tê, gedit ako lakisa numélo ya linie na ba linie nionso.
Polosi pona bobimisi nzoto lia lonkasa

column1: Specifies the font to use for a document's body when printing documents.
column3: Lakisa polosi ya kosalela mpona nzoto ya dokima ntango ya bobimisi.
Polosi pona bobimisi likolo lia lonkasa

column1: Specifies the font to use for page headers when printing a document. This will only take effect if the \"Print Header\" option is turned on.
column3: Lakisa polosi ya kosalela mpona likola lia lonkasa  ntango ya bobimisi dokima. Ekoki ko zwa esika soki liponi ya \"Bimisa likola lia lonksa\" ézali polele.
Polosi pona bobimisi numelo ya liniɛ

column1: Specifies the font to use for line numbers when printing. This will only take effect if the \"Print Line Numbers\" option is non-zero.
column3: Lakisa polosi ya kosalela mpona ba numelo ya linie ntango ya bobimisi.  Ekoki ko zwa esika soki liponi ya \"Bimisa numelo ya linie\" ézali zeló tê.

column1: List of candidate encodings shown in the Character Encoding menu in the open/save file chooser. \"CURRENT\" represents the current locale encoding. Only recognized encodings are used. The default value is the empty list, in which case gedit will choose good defaults depending on the country and language.
column3: Liste ya ba akɔdaze émonisami na ongele ya Fungola/bombisa mpe meni akɔdaze ya minkomá ya époniseli ya kasa. \"Ya sikawa\" élakisi akɔdaze ya minkomá ya sikawa. Kaka ba akɔdaze éyabani ndé ésalelami. Mpenza likwá ézali liste ya mpamba, na cas wana gedit akopono ya kitoko engebene na ekólo mpe lokóta na yo.

column1: List of active plugins. It contains the \"Location\" of the active plugins. See the .gedit-plugin file for obtaining the \"Location\" of a given plugin.
column3: Lisiti ya motingisa ngâ. Ezali na \"ésika\"  ya  motingisa ngâ. Tala kasa ya .gedit-plugin mpona kozwa \"ésika\" ya motingisi moko.

column1: A simple application to access, organize and share your documents on GNOME. It is meant to be a simple and elegant replacement for using a file manager to deal with documents. Seamless cloud integration is offered through GNOME Online Accounts.
column3: Esaleli ya mpamba pona koyingela, koyangela mpe kokabola ba dokima na yo na GNOME. Ntina na ye ezali kozala boponi ya mpamba mpe ya kitoko na bosaleli moyangeli ya ba kasa pona kosala ba dokima. Bokotisi ekokani na lipata ékoki kosela na konti Ɛtenɛ́ti ya GNOME.

column1: Nautilus, also known as Files, is the default file manager of the GNOME desktop. It provides a simple and integrated way of managing your files and browsing your file system.
column3: Nautilus, mpe eyebani lokola fisyé, ezali koyangela ba fisyé ya bilo ya GNOME. Ezali kosunga yo mpo na boyángeli ya ba fisyé na yo na kati ya lɔdinatɛ́lɛ.

column1: Nautilus supports all the basic functions of a file manager and more. It can search and manage your files and folders, both locally and on a network, read and write data to and from removable media, run scripts, and launch applications. It has three views: Icon Grid, Icon List, and Tree List. Its functions can be extended with plugins and scripts.
column3: Nautilus ezo salisa lolenge mpe motindo nini yako monisa, kobatela mpe kosala nyonso oyo olingi na ba fisyé. Ekoki kolukisa mpe kotambwisa ba fisyé na ba dosyé,na rézo to mpe na masini, kotanga mpe kobomba biloko na ba disiki,kopelisa mpe kotambwisa ba esaliseli.Ezali na lolenge ya kotalisa misato:griyaze ya Ikone, Ikone lolenge ya lístɛ, na lístɛ ya moété. Makoki mosusu ekoki kobakisama na botie plugin to ba skripte.

column1: Where to position newly open tabs in browser windows
column3: Esika ya kotia mapipi na lininisa ya Moluki

column1: If set to \"after-current-tab\", then new tabs are inserted after the current tab. If set to \"end\", then new tabs are appended to the end of the tab list.
column3: Soki otie \"after-current-tab\", nde lipipi ya sika etiami na sima ya lipipi oyo ozo salela. Soki otie na \"end\", nde lipipi ya sika etiami na suka ya ba lipipi nyonso.

column1: If set to true, then Nautilus browser windows will always use a textual input entry for the location toolbar, instead of the pathbar.

Esika ya ko salisa boluki bisika binso

column1: In which locations Nautilus should search on subfolders. Available values are 'local-only', 'always', 'never'.
column3: Esika nini Nautilus ekoki koluka ti na kati ya ba dosyé ya nsé.Ba mbenza bisengami bizali 'kaka na local', 'nseko','tɛ̂'.

column1: Filter the search dates using either last used or last modified.
column3: Pona eyano ya boluki na ndenge ya mokolo na ndenge esalemaki mokolo mwa suka to mpe bobalusi ya suka.

column3: Mpo na kolakisa biloko ya méni ya esíká oyo ekolimwa libela

column1: If set to true, then Nautilus will show a delete permanently context menu item to bypass the Trash.
column3: Soki otie na solo, Nautilus ekolakisa biloko ya méni ya esíká oyo elimwaki mpo na seko na bopimbwe Fulu.

column1: Whether to show context menu items to create links from copied or selected files
column3: Mpo na kolakisa biloko ya méni ya esíká mpo kokela ba ekangiseli wuta fisyé ya kopi to fisyé ba mpona

column1: If set to true, then Nautilus will show context menu items to create links from the copied or selected files.
column3: Soki otie solo, Nautilus ekolakisa biloko ya méni ya esíká mpo na kokela ba ekangiseli ewuta na fisyé ya kopi to ba fisyé bapona.

column1: Whether to ask for confirmation when deleting files, or emptying the Trash
column3: Mpo na kotuna soki olingi na ntango ya bolimwisi ba fisyé, to ntango ya bolimwisi biloko ya Fulu

column1: If set to true, then Nautilus will ask for confirmation when you attempt to delete files, or empty the Trash.
column3: Soki otie solo, Nautilus ekotuna yo yambo ya kolimwisa ba fisyé to mpe yambo yako limwisa biloko na Fulu.

column1: When to show number of items in a folder
column3: Ntango ya bomonisi limelo ya biloko na kati ya dosyé

column1: Speed tradeoff for when to show the number of items in a folder. If set to \"always\" then always show item counts, even if the folder is on a remote server. If set to \"local-only\" then only show counts for local file systems. If set to \"never\" then never bother to compute item counts.
column3: Mbangu na ntango ya kokomisa motuya ya fisyé na nkati ya dosyé.Soki otie na \"ntango-inso\" ekomonisa ntango inso motango ya fisyé, ata dosyé ezali na servere. Soki otie na \"kaka-ndaku\", kaka motango ya fisyé oya ndaku nde ekomonana. Soki otie na \"Tɛ̂\" motango moko tɛ̂ ekopesama.

column1: Type of click used to launch/open files
column3: Lolenge ya kokliker mpo na kokanga/kofungola ba fisyé

column1: Possible values are \"single\" to launch files on a single click, or \"double\" to launch them on a double click.
column3: Mituya esengami \"moko\" kofungola fisyé na klike moko, to mpe \"mibale\" kofungola fisyé na klike mibale elandana.

column1: What to do with executable text files when activated
column3: Nini ya kosala na ba fisyé koma oyo ekoki kotambwisama soki ezali ya ko lamuka

column1: What to do with executable text files when they are activated (single or double clicked). Possible values are \"launch\" to launch them as programs, \"ask\" to ask what to do via a dialog, and \"display\" to display them as text files.
column3: Nini kosala na fisyé oyo ekoki kotamwisama ntango ezali ya kolamwisama (klike moko to mpe mibale).Motuya ekoki kosengama mizali \"tambwisa\" mpo na kotamwisa lokola programe, \"tuna\" mpo na kotuna na efelo ya liyebisi, to mpe \"lakisa\" mpo na kolakisa lokola fisyé ya koma.

column1: Show the package installer for unknown MIME types
column3: Lakisa liboké ya kofandisa mpo na lolenge ya MIME oyo eyebani te

column1: Whether to show the user a package installer dialog in case an unknown MIME type is opened, in order to search for an application to handle it.
column3: Mpo na kolakisa mosaleli liboké ya kofandisa na ntango oyo lolenge MIME ezali ya kofungwama, na ntango ya boluki esaliseli ya kopelisa.

column1: For users with mice that have buttons for \"Forward\" and \"Back\", this key will set which button activates the \"Forward\" command in a browser window. Possible values range between 6 and 14.
column3: Mpo na basaleli ya souris nako fina buto \"Lekisa\" mpe \"Zonga\", túsi buto wana ekoluka buto nini ya ko lamuisa na ntango ya \"Lekisa\" na lininisa ya moluki.mbenza esengami bizali kati ya 6 ti 14.

column1: Mouse button to activate the \"Back\" command in browser window
column3: Buto ya souris mpo na kolamwisa camande ya \"bozongisi sima\" na kati ya lininisa ya muluki

column1: For users with mice that have buttons for \"Forward\" and \"Back\", this key will set which button activates the \"Back\" command in a browser window. Possible values range between 6 and 14.

column1: When to show thumbnails of files
column3: Ntango ya bolakisi bilili mike ya ba fisyé

column1: Speed trade-off for when to show a file as a thumbnail. If set to \"always\" then always thumbnail, even if the folder is on a remote server. If set to \"local-only\" then only show thumbnails for local file systems. If set to \"never\" then never bother to thumbnail files, just use a generic icon. Despite what the name may suggest, this applies to any previewable file type.
column3: Mbangu na ntango ya kokomisa fisyé na elili ya moke.Soki otie na \"ntango inso\" ekokoma ntango inso elili ya moke, ata dosyé ezali na servere. Soki otie na \"kaka-ndaku\" kaka elili ya moke ya fisyé oya ndaku nde ekomonana. Soki otie na \"Te\" elili ya moke moko te ekomonana, kaka ikone ya ba fisyé. Ata epesi yo nkombo, ekosala na lolenge ya bonisi liboso lolenge ya fisyé.
Bonene ya suka ya bilili ya mike

column1: Images over this size (in bytes) won't be thumbnailed. The purpose of this setting is to avoid thumbnailing large images that may take a long time to load or use lots of memory.
column3: Bilili na bonene oyo (na bytes) ekoki te kozua lolenge ya bilili ya muke.Palametele oyo ezali mpo na kopekisa bokomi moke ya bilili ya monene mpo ekoki kozua ngonga ebele na bofungoli oyo ekoki kozua memuále nyonso.
Lakisa yambo dosyé na kati ya maninisa

column3: Soki otie solo, Nautilus ekobanda yambo kolakisa ba fisyé na lolenge ya liste na ba ikone.

column1: The default sort-order for items in the icon view. Possible values are \"name\", \"size\", \"type\" and \"mtime\".

column1: Reverse sort order in new windows

column1: If true, files in new windows will be sorted in reverse order. I.e., if sorted by name, then instead of sorting the files from \"a\" to \"z\", they will be sorted from \"z\" to \"a\"; if sorted by size, instead of being incrementally they will be sorted decrementally.
column3: Soki otie solo, ba fisyé ya lininisa ekozala na molongo ya kobongwana.Lokola, soki olingi kolakisa ba fisyé na molongo ya nkombo kobanda \"a\" ti na \"z\", ekolakisama kobanda na \"z\" ti na \"a\"; soki olingi kolakisa na molongo ya bonene kobanda na \"moke\" ti na \"monene\", ekolakisa na molongo mwa \"bonene\" ti na ya \"moke\".
Komonisa dosyé na ntango ya bozangi

column1: When a folder is visited this viewer is used unless you have selected another view for that particular folder. Possible values are \"list-view\", and \"icon-view\".

column1: If set, Nautilus will append URIs of selected files and treat the result as a command line for bulk renaming. Bulk rename applications can register themselves in this key by setting the key to a space-separated string of their executable name and any command line options. If the executable name is not set to a full path, it will be searched for in the search path.

Bonene ya zume ya ikone na ndenge ya bozangi

Bonene ya zume ya bolakisi liste

column1: An integer specifying how parts of overlong file names should be replaced by ellipses on the desktop. If the number is larger than 0, the file name will not exceed the given number of lines. If the number is 0 or smaller, no limit is imposed on the number of displayed lines.
column3: Antiyé ezo lakisa lolenge ya boleki molayi na nkombo ya fisyé ekoki kokitana na ba elipse likolo ya bilo. Soki motuya eleki 0 na molayi, nkombo ya fisyé ekoleka te motuya opesi na ba linye. Soki motuya opesi eza moke na 0, oza na mondelu te mpo na motuya na ba linye oyo ekomonana.

column3: Bonene ya bozangi ya pano ya mopanzi na kati ya lininisa.
